<Group labelreference="L19" drawlabel="true">
<Input>
<Text-field style="Text" size="16" layout="Normal"><Font size="16">The solid body vortex is kind of the opposite limit of the irrotational vortex.  Because the rotation is a solid body rotation, the rate of strain matrix is identically zero, while the vorticity is constant everywhere.  Real vortices are a mix of the two cases (google the Rankine, or Kida vortex if you want to see more).</Font></Text-field>
</Input>
</Group>
<Group labelreference="L7">
<Input>
<Text-field prompt="&gt; " style="Maple Input" layout="Normal"></Text-field>
</Input>
</Group>
<Group labelreference="L20" drawlabel="true">
<Input>
<Text-field style="Text" size="16" layout="Normal"><Font size="16">The second part of the worksheet is purely recreational and considers potential flow.  The potential I give is easily derived via conformal maps from complex analysis, but these are often the very last thing done in complex variables courses, or completely skipped.  Nevertheless at one point such maps were the dominant method for solving fluids problems.  Even now, conformal maps based algorithms are the state of the art for certain subclasses of problems.</Font></Text-field>
</Input>
</Group>
<Group labelreference="L8">
<Input>
<Text-field prompt="&gt; " style="Maple Input" layout="Normal">phi:=simplify((sqrt(x*x+y*y)^n)*cos(n*arctan(y/x)));</Text-field>
</Input>
<Output>
<Text-field style="2D Output" layout="Maple Output"><Equation executable="false" style="2D Output" display="">KiYpLCYqJClJInhHNiIiIiMiIiJGKiokKUkieUdGKEYpRipGKiwkKiYjRipGKUYqSSJuR0YoRipGKkYqLUkkY29zRzYkJSpwcm90ZWN0ZWRHSShfc3lzbGliR0YoNiMqJkYxRiotSSdhcmN0YW5HRjQ2IyomRi1GKkYnISIiRipGKg==</Equation></Text-field>
</Output>
</Group>
<Group labelreference="L9">
<Input>
<Text-field prompt="&gt; " style="Maple Input" layout="Normal">uwall:=simplify(diff(phi,x));</Text-field>
</Input>
<Output>
<Text-field style="2D Output" layout="Maple Output"><Equation executable="false" style="2D Output" display="">KigpLCYqJClJInhHNiIiIiMiIiJGKiokKUkieUdGKEYpRipGKiwmKiYjRipGKUYqSSJuR0YoRipGKkYqISIiRipGMUYqLCYqJkYnRiotSSRjb3NHNiQlKnByb3RlY3RlZEdJKF9zeXNsaWJHRig2IyomRjFGKi1JJ2FyY3RhbkdGNzYjKiZGLUYqRidGMkYqRipGKiomLUkkc2luR0Y3RjpGKkYtRipGKkYq</Equation></Text-field>
</Output>
</Group>
